The Dow Jones Industrial Average is flat Monday afternoon with shares of Merck and Chevron delivering the strongest returns for the price-weighted average. The Dow DJIA, -0.57% was most recently trading at 25,605, unchanged from yesterday's close. Merck's shares have fallen $1.98 (2.6%) while those of Chevron have dropped $1.62, or 1.8%, combining for a roughly 25-point drag on the Dow. Also contributing significantly are Pfizer PFE, -0.11%, Home Depot HD, -0.77%, and IBM IBM, 0.73%. A $1 move in any one of the 30 components of the benchmark results in a 6.86-point swing.

